description:
Recently sold: $440,000. If you would like to see this property, please contact Russ and Christie at 763.286.6617  For a Virtual Tour:  https://www.fsbohomes.com/virtualopenhousetour.asp

This stunning 2,743 sq. foot (4,400 total) modified two story, custom built home is located in a desirable, family friendly neighborhood close to nearby parks, a YMCA Community Center and within walking distance to District 11 Schools.  Every detail was carefully custom designed, and quality crafted by Hammer Custom Homes.  This is a one owner, two-person home which has only been occupied for a portion of each year.  The grand entryway with soaring 18 foot vaulted ceilings draws you into the open floor plan with two family rooms on the main level, two cozy gas fireplaces, an elegant formal dining room, a loft with a sunlit solar tube overlooking the spacious great room and french doors to the home office.  This home features wall to wall windows and a solar tube which brings in a lot of natural sunlight.  The main floor has upgraded 9 foot ceilings throughout with an 18? ceiling in the great room and an 11 foot ceiling in the office.   The great room contains a beautiful gas fireplace with stone to the ceiling, while the family room features an additional black granite gas fireplace.  The impeccable kitchen features a large island that seats seven, maple cabinets, tile backsplash, Silestone counter-tops, under cabinet lighting, stainless-steel appliances and a walk-in pantry.   The large master suite encompasses a walk-in closet, luxurious two-person Jacuzzi tub, dual sinks, dual shower heads and gorgeous tile-work.  

The landscaped exterior features a high-efficiency smart irrigation system, professional outdoor LED architectural and landscape lighting, a large cedar deck and wiring for your future hot tub.   With a south-facing backyard, you can enjoy the sunlight on the peaceful large cedar deck.  The 1650 sq. ft. walkout basement with a roughed-in wet bar, full bath, and 4th bathroom is ready to be finished for your family to enjoy.  The open floor plan basement is upgraded with engineered floor trusses containing plumbing, HVAC, and electrical which allows for higher ceiling heights, fewer beams, and no soffits.  The three-car garage has been extended to accommodate a boat, trailer or additional storage needs.  This home is sure to go fast.

The owner is willing to pay $3,000 to the buyer?s agent.

description: Recently sold: $334,500. Recently sold: $249,900. This 4 bedroom, 2 bath home shouts out pride of ownership! Features include wood floors in the kitchen and living room, laminate in the main level bedrooms.  Double closet in Master. The kitchen will have a new dishwasher, and has many cabinets, portable center island with patio doors to a large deck over looking large fenced back yard. Lower level is finished with a family room, completely remodeled bathroom with a 4x5 ceramic shower and 2 bedrooms (1 bedroom currently a dressing room!) Ceramic tile floors in Lower level, family room has a walkout to large 16x14 patio and walk up to the garage. New features: Brand Exterior vinyl siding and central air were new in 2019, Furnace 2003, Shingles 2012. The sellers have enjoyed this home and are excited to see a new family enjoy as they have. Conveniently located just blocks off Highway 65, close but far enough to enjoy peace and tranquility!The seller will escrow money at closing for an new septic system to be installed.

Recently sold: $225,000. Looking for a home where you can earn instant equity? This split entry walkout is on a gorgeous 1.05-acre lot with mature trees, 2 stall attached garage & 1 stall detached garage with a workbench on a private corner lot. Two wood-burning fireplaces & a maintenance-free deck off the informal dining area. Lower level office would need a closet to be a bedroom.

description: Recently sold: $287,000. A rare opportunity to own a home in Woodland Creek.  This original owner town home has been impeccably cared for, non-smoking and no pets. The Woodland Creek Town homes are side-by-side with the only connecting wall being between the garages.  This unit has an unfinished basement, with plenty of room to add additional bedrooms and a rough in for another bathroom.  The upstairs offers an open concept kitchen/dining/livingroom with plenty of room for a large dining room table.  The kitchen offers a center island and plenty of counter space and cupboards.  Off the living room is a 13x13 sun room that leads out to the concrete patio.  The welcoming large foyer in this unit has a nice bench to sit down and remove your shoes, and plenty of closet space for coats and shoes. The oversized two car garage has plenty of room for a work bench and also has a door going to the back of the home for easy access to back yard and patio.

description: Recently sold: $631,500. Where to begin on the story of this home? Gorgeous 3.03 acre private lot that is enhanced with a pond that wraps around to the back.  I tried to tell a story with the photos & there is a supplement available to tell you the almost innumerable features. You really need to come & experience the home for the benefits provided by the features. The sunroom is really a 4 season porch & in addition to all the natural light, it has access to the teak, yes, I said teak deck.  The upper level has Cherry cabinetry (even on the refrigerator, dishwasher & trash compactor) & Brazilian Cherry floors.  Kitchen has a walk in pantry, double stainless oven, raised dishwasher, slate back splash & granite counter tops.  There is even a hearth room feel with the pier fireplace. Owner's suite is simply sumptuous. The lower level has Maple woodwork thru out.    Recent updates include a new roof in July 2018 & 2 Phase High Efficiency Furnace in 2017.  There is a 2nd 3 car garage under the main garage. See it!

description:
Recently sold: $665,000. 14 acres of pure bliss at this ranch so close to town! #horsefarm #homeforsale #hobbyfarm 
THE most blissful hobby farm/ranch is for sale where the horses can run! 
An 80x60 outbuilding has a 14x14 RV door, and a 36x36 horse stable has 5 stalls and a tack room! A huge shed with a concrete floor holds all the maintenance items needed to keep the land and gardens lush and lavish. 
Rolling terrain pleases the eye and a pretty pond is an added bonus. 
Brick and real stone enhance the beauty of this dwelling that is surrounded by white vinyl fencing. 
An upper-level deck wraps around the home above the insulated 3 car garage and is accessible from the 3 season porch that is just off the big family room! 
Entertain guests in the rec room that has a full wet bar with seating while gazing out at the land beyond. 
Tall oak cabinets, wood flooring, a center island, recipe desk, vaulted ceiling, and tons of natural light grace the massive kitchen and the casual dining area is decadent while the open floor plan flows into the main level living space with a toasty fireplace. 
Be the Master of this domain in the bedroom sanctuary with a race track ceiling and coved trim and a warm walk-thru bath. 
Enjoy the bliss that this incredible ranch style home has to offer! 
By the Chris Fritch Team Keller Williams Classic Realty 763-746-3997

Gorgeous Executive 2 story home in a beautiful neighborhood. 5 Bedroom 4 Bath, 4 Season Porch, 4 car Heated Garage, Hardwood Floors, Granite Counter Tops, Tiled Back Splash, New Sinks/Faucets, New Furnace and Water Heater 14 x 24 Mait Free Deck, New Carpet upstairs, Fresh Paint, Stunning Master Suite with his and hers Sinks. THIS HOME IS A MUST SEE!!
Recently sold: $1,055,000.

Recently sold: $129,000. The property states 1009 square feet this is not including the basements square footage. Newer windows with in the last 10 years threw the entire house. Two car heated garage attached to the house and the cement is sealed. Their is also a newer ( with in the last 10 years) garage in the back yead. This is also heated and has electricity running to It this makes for a perfect man cave.  Sprinkler system which was connected to the well to save money after switching the inside of house to city water, fenced yard.  The grill on the deck is connected to the natural gas line for out door grilling.  The deck was rebuilt with composite decking to keep it from wearing away in these MN winter's and a retaining wall was built partially around dect to prevent erosan. The house has also had the roof replaced and stucco siding added on the outside. The kitchen has new cabinets, sink, wood floors, gard rail, patio door and appliances. Living room was remodeled with wood flooring, egressed window new front door and closet doors. Hall way basic with wood flooring. All three bedroom have new wood flooring closets and doors.  The bathroom has tile flooring just basic bathroom with tub lotts of storage space. The basement has a huge recreation room with 2 closets on opposite sides of each other this floor is carpeted. The bathroom in the basement is a little different it has a sink and toilet and window when you go out of the bathroom to your right their is a shower it is closed in but kind of a awkward spot..  It was probably done this way to save from having to rip out the hole bathroom and start over. The laundry room, pantry and under the stairwell and open room are not finished and their is also a door to walk out to your back yard.  My dad worked hard on this property to make sure that  the house was  ready for when he retired. Unfortunately he never made it to that day.
